{
  "texts": [
    "This chain combines advanced retrieval techniques with question-answering capabilities, allowing us to efficiently extract relevant information from process model data.",
    "The chain first performs a retrieval step to fetch relevant chunks, then it passes those textual segments into an LLM to generate a response.To leverage qDrant within the RetrievalQA chain, a qDrant client needs to be configured as the retriever component.",
    "Such client interacts with the qDrant vector index, querying it to retrieve process model chunks that are relevant to user queries.Through experimental analysis, we also determined the optimal number of chunks that yields optimal results.",
    "This number was found to strike a balance between providing sufficient context for generating accurate answers and respecting the context window of the language model.",
    "Retrieving a sufficient number of process model chunks is fundamental for ensuring that the retrieved content contains all the necessary context for generating accurate answers."
  ]
}